Explanation of results:

- I inspected routes/productRoutes.js and controllers/productController.js. The router mounts POST /api/products and it applies the middleware protect and admin before calling createProduct.
- The createProduct controller creates a Product document with the Mongoose Product model (see models/productModel.js) and returns the created product in the response with HTTP status 201.
- Because the route is protected by authentication/authorization middleware, typical responses include 401 Unauthorized (authentication missing/invalid) and 403 Forbidden (authenticated but not admin). The controller itself returns 201 on success. Server errors can occur, so include 500 Internal Server Error.
- I derived the product structure from models/productModel.js (including review schema and timestamps). Per the instruction, the Response Objects do not use $ref and instead include inline schemas for the successful 201 response. Other responses include plain descriptions.

